title: Rogers rolls over Shadle Park, Mead stomps Ferris
text:
Rogers rolls over Shadle Park, Mead stomps Ferris Published On: Oct 15 2015 10:48:20 PM PDT Tweet SPOKANE, Wash. - 
For the first time since 2000, the Rogers football team has won at least three games after edging out Shadle Park, 30-14 on Thursday night. 
Pirates senior quarterback Cole Shafer finished 19 of 25 for 149 yards and two touchdowns. Rogers improves to (3-4). 
In the second half of the doubleheader, Mead led Ferris 17-7 at the break before an offensive outburst in the second half as they rolled, 45-7. 
Panthers quarterback Payton Loucks completed 9-of-18 passes for 221 yards and four scores and while running back EJ Bade racked up 90 yards on the ground and two TD's through the air.
